(103, 1, '2014-05-20 11:38:31', '2014-05-20 11:38:31', 'Jeremy Summers began developing for the web over 10 years ago, and quickly launched a music streaming website as a personal project. Such enjoyment was found he decided to formalise his hobby by returning to college to embark on 4 years of higher education, culminating with a First in BSc (hons) Applied Computing, and an official letter of commendation. During some of this time he interned at <a href="http://www.spicerack.co.uk" title="Spicerack" target="_blank">Spicerack Media Ltd</a>,  ', 'About', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '11-revision-v1', '', '', '2014-05-20 11:38:31', '2014-05-20 11:38:31', '', 11, 'http://wizard.technology/11-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(104, 1, '2014-05-20 12:54:51', '2014-05-20 12:54:51', 'Jeremy Summers began developing for the web over 10 years ago, and quickly launched a music streaming website as a personal project. Such enjoyment was found he decided to formalise his hobby by returning to college to embark on 4 years of higher education, culminating with a First in BSc (hons) Applied Computing, and an official letter of commendation. During some of this time he interned at <a href="http://www.spicerack.co.uk" title="Spicerack" target="_blank">Spicerack Media Ltd</a>, where he applied some of his skills to real world tasks. Following completion of his degree, Jeremy took a full time position as Head of Technology at Spicerack, where he worked for three more years, developing bespoke online/digital solutions for National and global brands including, Estée Lauder, Philosophy, Sky, Science in Sport, Homebase, and Garnier, as well as managing the internal technology needs of Spicerack, including build and maintenance of the company website and intranet. \r\n\r\nRecently Jeremy decided to go it alone, allowing him to spend more time ...\r\n\r\nIn his spare time Jeremy likes to compete in cycling time trials, something he actually plans to be good at one day - although this hasn''t happened in over 25 years of competitive cycling!\r\n\r\n', 'About', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '11-revision-v1', '', '', '2014-05-20 12:54:51', '2014-05-20 12:54:51', '', 11, 'http://wizard.technology/11-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(105, 1, '2014-05-20 13:14:10', '2014-05-20 13:14:10', 'Jeremy Summers began developing for the web over 10 years ago, and quickly launched a music streaming website as a personal project. Such enjoyment was found he decided to formalise his hobby by returning to college to embark on 4 years of higher education, culminating with a First in BSc (hons) Applied Computing, and an official letter of commendation. During some of this time he interned at <a href="http://www.spicerack.co.uk" title="Spicerack" target="_blank">Spicerack Media Ltd</a>, where he applied some of his skills to real world tasks. Following completion of his degree, Jeremy took a full time position as Head of Technology at Spicerack, where he worked for three more years, developing bespoke online/digital solutions for National and global brands including, Estée Lauder, Philosophy, Sky, Science in Sport, Homebase, and Garnier, as well as managing the internal technology needs of Spicerack, including build and maintenance of the company website,intranet and servers.\r\n\r\nRecently Jeremy decided to go it alone, allowing him to spend more time working and less time travelling.\r\n\r\nIn his spare time Jeremy likes to train and compete in cycling time trials, something he plans to be good at one day - although this hasn''t happened in over 25 years of competitive cycling!\r\n\r\n', 'About', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '11-revision-v1', '', '', '2014-05-20 13:14:10', '2014-05-20 13:14:10', '', 11, 'http://wizard.technology/11-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(106, 1, '2014-05-20 13:24:44', '2014-05-20 13:24:44', 'Jeremy Summers began developing for the web over 10 years ago, and quickly launching a music streaming website. He decided to formalise his craft by returning to college to complete 4 years of higher education, culminating with a First in BSc (hons) Applied Computing, with an official letter of commendation. During some of this time he interned at <a href="http://www.spicerack.co.uk" title="Spicerack" target="_blank">Spicerack Media Ltd</a>, where he applied some of his skills to real world tasks. Following completion of his degree, Jeremy took a full time position as Head of Technology at Spicerack, where he worked for three more years, developing bespoke online/digital solutions for National and global brands including, Estée Lauder, Philosophy, Sky, Science in Sport, Homebase, and Garnier, as well as managing the internal technology needs of Spicerack, including the building and maintenance of the company website, intranet and servers.\r\n\r\nRecently Jeremy decided to start Wizard Technology, allowing him to spend more time working and less time travelling, as well as focusing more heavily on data-driven system development. Jeremy is looking forward to meeting new clients\r\n\r\nIn his spare time Jeremy likes to train and compete in cycling time trials, something he plans to be good at one day - although this hasn''t happened in over 25 years of competitive cycling! In fact, Wizard Technology has plans to build an analytical database for power based training in 2014.\r\n\r\n', 'About', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '11-revision-v1', '', '', '2014-05-20 13:24:44', '2014-05-20 13:24:44', '', 11, 'http://wizard.technology/11-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(107, 1, '2014-05-20 13:26:28', '2014-05-20 13:26:28', 'Jeremy Summers began developing for the web over 10 years ago, and quickly launching a music streaming website. He decided to formalise his craft by returning to college to complete 4 years of higher education, culminating with a First in BSc (hons) Applied Computing, with an official letter of commendation. During some of this time he interned at <a href="http://www.spicerack.co.uk" title="Spicerack" target="_blank">Spicerack Media Ltd</a>, where he applied some of his skills to real world tasks. Following completion of his degree, Jeremy took a full time position as Head of Technology at Spicerack, where he worked for three more years, developing bespoke online/digital solutions for National and global brands including, Estée Lauder, Philosophy, Sky, Science in Sport, Homebase, and Garnier, as well as managing the internal technology needs of Spicerack, including the building and maintenance of the company website, intranet and servers.\r\n\r\nJeremy recently decided to start Wizard Technology, allowing him to spend more time working and less time travelling, as well as focusing more heavily on data-driven system development. Jeremy is looking forward to helping new clients increase traffic to their own businesses.\r\n\r\nIn his spare time Jeremy likes to train and compete in cycling time trials, something he plans to be good at one day - although this hasn''t happened in over 25 years of competitive cycling! In fact, Wizard Technology has plans to build an analytical database for power based training in 2014.\r\n\r\n', 'About', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '11-revision-v1', '', '', '2014-05-20 13:26:28', '2014-05-20 13:26:28', '', 11, 'http://wizard.technology/11-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(108, 1, '2014-05-20 13:31:08', '2014-05-20 13:31:08', 'Jeremy Summers began developing for the web over 10 years ago, and quickly launching a music streaming website. He decided to formalise his craft by returning to college to complete 4 years of higher education, culminating with a First in BSc (hons) Applied Computing, with an official letter of commendation. During some of this time he interned at <a href="http://www.spicerack.co.uk" title="Spicerack" target="_blank">Spicerack Media Ltd</a>, where he applied some of his skills to real world tasks. Following completion of his degree, Jeremy took a full time position as Head of Technology at Spicerack, where he worked for three more years, developing bespoke online/digital solutions for National and global brands including, Estée Lauder, Philosophy, Sky, Science in Sport, Homebase, and Garnier, as well as managing the internal technology needs of Spicerack, including the building and maintenance of the company website, intranet and servers.\r\n\r\nJeremy recently decided to start <a href="http://wizard.technology">Wizard Technology</a>, allowing him to spend more time working and less time travelling, as well as focusing more heavily on data-driven system development. Jeremy is looking forward to helping new clients increase traffic to their own businesses.\r\n\r\nIn his spare time Jeremy likes to train and compete in cycling time trials, something he plans to be good at one day - although this hasn''t happened in over 25 years of competitive cycling! In fact, Wizard Technology has plans to build an analytical database for power based training in 2014. \r\n\r\n', 'About', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '11-revision-v1', '', '', '2014-05-20 13:31:08', '2014-05-20 13:31:08', '', 11, 'http://wizard.technology/11-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(109, 1, '2014-05-20 13:32:04', '2014-05-20 13:32:04', 'Jeremy Summers began developing for the web over 10 years ago, and quickly launching a music streaming website. He decided to formalise his craft by returning to college to complete 4 years of higher education, culminating with a First in BSc (hons) Applied Computing, with an official letter of commendation. During some of this time he interned at <a href="http://www.spicerack.co.uk" title="Spicerack" target="_blank">Spicerack Media Ltd</a>, where he applied some of his skills to real world tasks. Following completion of his degree, Jeremy took a full time position as Head of Technology at Spicerack, where he worked for three more years, developing bespoke online/digital solutions for National and global brands including, Estée Lauder, Philosophy, Sky, Science in Sport, Homebase, and Garnier, as well as managing the internal technology needs of Spicerack, including the building and maintenance of the company website, intranet and servers.\r\n\r\nJeremy recently decided to start <a href="http://wizard.technology">Wizard Technology</a>, allowing him to spend more time working and less time travelling, as well as focusing more heavily on data-driven system development. Jeremy is looking forward to helping new clients increase traffic to their own businesses.\r\n\r\nIn his spare time Jeremy likes to train and compete in <a href="http://www.cyclingtimetrials.org.uk/" title="CTT" target="_blank">cycling time trials</a>, something he plans to be good at one day - although this hasn''t happened in over 25 years of competitive cycling! In fact, Wizard Technology has plans to build an analytical database for power based training in 2014. \r\n\r\n', 'About', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '11-revision-v1', '', '', '2014-05-20 13:32:04', '2014-05-20 13:32:04', '', 11, 'http://wizard.technology/11-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(110, 1, '2014-05-20 13:52:09', '2014-05-20 13:52:09', 'Jeremy Summers began developing for the web over 10 years ago, and quickly launching a music streaming website. He decided to formalise his craft by returning to college to complete 4 years of higher education, culminating with a First in BSc (hons) Applied Computing, with an official letter of commendation. During some of this time he interned at <a href="http://www.spicerack.co.uk" title="Spicerack" target="_blank">Spicerack Media Ltd</a>, where he applied some of his skills to real world tasks. Following completion of his degree, Jeremy took a full time position as Head of Technology at Spicerack, where he worked for three more years, developing bespoke online/digital solutions for National and global brands including, Estée Lauder, Philosophy, Sky, Science in Sport, Homebase, and Garnier, as well as managing the internal technology needs of Spicerack, including the building and maintenance of the company website, intranet and servers.\r\n\r\nJeremy recently decided to start Exmoor based <a href="http://wizard.technology">Wizard Technology</a>, allowing him to spend more time working and less time travelling, as well as focusing more heavily on data-driven system development. Jeremy is looking forward to helping new clients increase traffic to their own businesses.\r\n\r\nIn his spare time Jeremy likes to train and compete in <a href="http://www.cyclingtimetrials.org.uk/" title="CTT" target="_blank">cycling time trials</a>, something he plans to be good at one day - although this hasn''t happened in over 25 years of competitive cycling! In fact, Wizard Technology has plans to build an analytical database for power based training in 2014. \r\n\r\n', 'About', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '11-revision-v1', '', '', '2014-05-20 13:52:09', '2014-05-20 13:52:09', '', 11, 'http://wizard.technology/11-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
