(1803, 1, '2014-05-29 12:54:23', '2014-05-29 12:54:23', 'Wizard Technology founder Jeremy Summers began developing for the web over 10 years ago, and quickly launched a music streaming website. Following a move to the South West Jeremy took a full time position as Head of Technology at <a href="http://www.spicerack.co.uk" title="Spicerack" target="_blank">Spicerack Media Ltd</a>, where he worked for four years, developing bespoke online/digital solutions for National and global brands including, Estée Lauder, Philosophy, Sky, Science in Sport, Homebase, and Garnier, as well as managing the internal technology needs of Spicerack, including the building and maintenance of the company website, intranet and servers.\r\n\r\nJeremy recently decided to start Exmoor based <a href="http://wizard.technology">Wizard Technology</a>, allowing him to spend more time working and less time travelling, as well as focusing more heavily on data-driven system development. Jeremy is looking forward to helping new clients increase traffic to their own businesses.\r\n\r\nHaving been a competitive cyclist for many years, Jeremy loves to train and compete in <a href="http://www.cyclingtimetrials.org.uk/" title="CTT" target="_blank">Cycling Time Trials</a>, which he finds to contain the perfect balance of technology, analysis, determination and fun! In fact, Wizard Technology has plans to build an analytical database for power based training in 2014. \r\n\r\nJeremy also has a First-class honours degree in Applied Computing (<abbr title="Bachelor of Science">BSc</abbr>), with an official letter of commendation. \r\n\r\n', 'About', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '11-revision-v1', '', '', '2014-05-29 12:54:23', '2014-05-29 12:54:23', '', 11, 'http://wizard.technology/11-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
